properties.Title: Santa Clara County House Party
properties.Description:
Please join me:

House Party to Support Andrew Yang

Friday, February 21 at 5 PM

Evan Dowling

1750 Curtner Avenue, San Jose, CA 95124

408-483-3431

Share some food and learn more about why so many folks think Andrew Yang is the best choice for President.

And learn why Yang's proposed Universal Basic Income of $1,000 a month for every adult American citizen would be a game changer in combating homelessness while strengthening middle class families across America, particularly in Santa Clara County.

Bring a friend or two.

In my view, electing someone on simply hating Trump might be successful, but it will not result in an electoral mandate for positive change to address the challenges of the 21st century.

And going back to the status quo before Trump got elected is not the answer, given the crisis of ever increasing income inequality due to the growing power of special interest lobbyists.

We need fresh solutions from an energetic and forward thinking expert on technology.

Andrew Yang is one of the top six finalists in the California primary, polling ahead of Amy Klobuchar, Tom Steyer and Tulsi Gabbard and is closing in on Mike Bloomberg and Pete Buttigieg.

At the house party I will have information on how to vote in the Democratic presidential primary if you are not currently a registered voter or a registered Democrat. We will also discuss why Andrew Yang is the best candidate to defeat Donald Trump.

We can do better and leave no one behind, led by a positive, forward-looking and inspirational tech entrepreneur.

Andrew Yang's slogan for his campaign is MATH: Make America Think Harder. A great slogan, and much needed.

I look forward to seeing you at my happy house party at 5 PM on Friday, February 21.

Best regards,

Evan Dowling

Feb 3: Voter Registration Deadline Feb 12-25: Early Voting Begins March 3: Primary Voting (TN is a Super Tuesday state!)
